                     annotation:naturalLanguageDefinition "A DesignedFunction that is realized in a SealingProcess and that consists in providing a tight interface against which a closure element bears to prevent fluid leakage through a valve."@en .


###  https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SealingProcess
copi:SealingProcess rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:label "processo de vedação"@pt-br ,
                               "sealing process"@en ;
                    skos:definition "A PlannedProcess in which a valve seat provides a sealing interface for a closure element (gate, ball, disc) to bear against, preventing fluid passage when the valve is closed."@en ;
                    annotation:naturalLanguageDefinition "A PlannedProcess in which a valve seat provides a sealing interface for a closure element (gate, ball, disc) to bear against, preventing fluid passage when the valve is closed."@en .


